g, and with averted eyes, explained that the diamond brooch, an empress’s gift to her great-grandmother, had been pawned to obtain the money for Ardalion’s journey, as his friend had not repaid him.

“All right, all right, don’t howl,” I said, pocketing the pawn ticket. “Deuced cunning of him. Thank God he’s gone, scuttled away—that’s the main thing.”

